---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="llm-contract — Reliability boundary for LLM output"
  description="Treat LLM output as untrusted input. llm-contract enforces a deterministic acceptance boundary for structured outputs."
>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-14">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_320px] gap-10 items-start">
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-zinc-500 mb-4">Overview</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white tracking-tight leading-tight">
          JSON shape is not correctness.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-lg mt-6 max-w-3xl">
          <span class="text-zinc-200 font-medium">llm-contract</span> wraps any LLM call in a deterministic contract:
          clean output, validate schema and invariants, classify failures, generate targeted repair feedback, retry within policy.
        </p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm mt-4 max-w-3xl">
          Accepted output always passed runtime checks. Otherwise you get explicit failure details.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-8">
          <a href="quickstart" class="glass rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-accent card-hover text-sm">Start with Quickstart</a>
          <a href="how-it-works" class="glass rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-accent card-hover text-sm">Understand the contract loop</a>
          <a href="#failure-moment" class="glass rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-accent card-hover text-sm">See the failure moment</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="glass rounded-xl p-5 lg:mt-8">
        <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-500 font-semibold mb-2">Attempt trace</p>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm font-mono">
          <div class="rounded border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5 px-3 py-2"><span class="text-red-400">Attempt 1 · PARSE_ERROR</span></div>
          <div class="rounded border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/5 px-3 py-2"><span class="text-amber-400">Attempt 2 · INVARIANT_ERROR</span></div>
          <div class="rounded border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5 px-3 py-2"><span class="text-emerald-400">Attempt 3 · SUCCESS</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
          <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500 mb-1">Boundary rule</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-zinc-300">The model proposes output. Your contract decides acceptance.</p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="failure-moment" class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">The failure moment in real systems</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-7 max-w-3xl">
      The pain appears at the output handoff: model text enters parsing, validation, and application logic.
    </p>
    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 max-w-3xl mb-6">
      <p class="font-mono text-sm text-zinc-300">LLM -> response -> parse -> validate -> application logic -> failure</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-4 card-hover"><p class="text-white font-medium text-sm">Malformed JSON</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-4 card-hover"><p class="text-white font-medium text-sm">Invalid schema fields</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-4 card-hover"><p class="text-white font-medium text-sm">Cross-field contradictions</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-4 card-hover"><p class="text-white font-medium text-sm">Retries that do not converge</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-4 card-hover"><p class="text-white font-medium text-sm">Silent bad routing decisions</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-4 card-hover"><p class="text-white font-medium text-sm">Invalid downstream writes</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">How the deterministic boundary fixes it</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-7 max-w-3xl">This boundary enforces runtime acceptance criteria before output can affect your system.</p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
        <p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">instructions + verify</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Normalizes output and enforces structural correctness.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
        <p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">invariants + classification</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Catches domain violations and identifies exact failure class.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
        <p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">repair + bounded retry</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Feeds targeted corrections back to the model within explicit retry policy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm mt-6 font-mono">instructions -> clean -> verify(schema + invariants) -> classify -> repair -> retry -> typed result or explicit failure</p>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">Where this is worth adding</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
        <ul class="text-zinc-300 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>Classification and routing systems.</li>
          <li>Extraction and normalization pipelines.</li>
          <li>Agent tool output validation.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
        <ul class="text-zinc-300 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>Financial, healthcare, and compliance-sensitive automation.</li>
          <li>Workflows where bad output has operational cost.</li>
          <li>Teams replacing brittle parse/validate/retry glue code.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm mt-6">Skip for free-form chat where structural correctness does not matter.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">Trust signals</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-sm text-zinc-300">Explicit failure taxonomy</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-sm text-zinc-300">Bounded retry policies</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-sm text-zinc-300">Typed success or explicit failure</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-sm text-zinc-300">Provider-agnostic model integration</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-sm text-zinc-300">One runtime dependency (`zod`)</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-sm text-zinc-300">Test-backed core behavior</p></div>
    </div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">What llm-contract is not</h3>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-sm text-zinc-300">Not an LLM framework</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-sm text-zinc-300">Not an agent system</p></div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-sm text-zinc-300">Not an orchestration layer</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-sm">
      <a href="quickstart" class="glass rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-accent card-hover">Open Quickstart</a>
      <a href="how-it-works" class="glass rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-accent card-hover">Read How It Works</a>
      <a href="api" class="glass rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-accent card-hover">Read Core API</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
